# Home Payment Atlas — repo hygiene
#
# Policy: keep the small, REQUIRED launch data tracked; ignore the large OPTIONAL
# expansion datasets. A full Zillow refresh writes ~600 MB into /csv (City/Metro/
# ZIP/County ZHVI + ZORI rent files). Committing those every month would bloat git
# history irreversibly, so we ignore them here. City/metro/rent PAGES are not built
# yet — when they are, we'll revisit this policy deliberately.
#
# NOTE: deleting these files from the working tree (or this ignore rule) only keeps
# NEW versions out of history. It does NOT remove versions already committed. If big
# CSVs were ever committed, shrinking the repo requires a one-time history rewrite
# (git filter-repo or BFG) + force-push. See README "Repository size note".

# --- Tracked on purpose (do NOT ignore) ---
#   csv/State_*.csv            ← required state launch ZHVI data
#   csv/zillow-manifest.json   ← machine-readable manifest

# --- Ignored: large optional expansion CSVs ---
csv/City_*.csv
csv/Metro_*.csv
csv/County_*.csv
csv/Zip_*.csv
csv/Neighborhood_*.csv
csv/National_*.csv
csv/Us_*.csv
# Any ZORI/rent file regardless of geography prefix
csv/*_zori_*.csv
# Optional payment datasets, if they ever ship as large files
csv/*mortgage_payment*.csv
csv/*total_monthly_payment*.csv

# --- Standard ignores ---
node_modules/
.DS_Store
*.log
